    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Circular, flat-sided bases, often made of wood; used in conjunction with gavels to communicate particular actions or to gather attention; accomplished by striking the gavel block with the mallet. Examples of use include court proceedings or auctions. </Note_Text>
